Package core

Class GameLogic

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.GameLogic
  • public class GameLogic
extends java.lang.Object
    GameLogic is a class that represents the game logic for the game. It handles the game rules, player turns, and dice rolls.

    • Method Detail

      • rollDice

        public void rollDice​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer> snakes,
                     java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer> ladders)
        Rolls the dice and moves the current player forward by the number of spaces rolled. If the player lands on a snake, they are moved back to the snake's tail. If the player lands on a ladder, they are moved up to the ladder's top.
        Parameters:
        snakes - HashMap of snakes
        ladders - HashMap of ladders

      • isGameOver

        public boolean isGameOver()
        Checks if the game is over. The game is over if either player has reached the end of the board.
        Returns:
        true if the game is over, false otherwise
